OL,3,CPaterson: Five years on, what action
OL,4,Chas been taken to stop criminal
OL,5,Csurgeons?
OL,7,FIn April 2017 he was found guilty of
OL,8,Fwounding ten patients in the private
OL,9,Fsector by exaggerating or inventing
OL,10,Ftheir risk of cancer to carry out
OL,11,Funnecessary operations, including
OL,12,Fperforming mastectomies on women who
OL,13,Fdid not have the disease.
OL,15,FA month later he was jailed for 15
OL,16,Fyears, but that was increased to 20
OL,17,Fyears on appeal.
